nd exegetical texts. The contributors include established scholars of the field and early-career researchers."--Publisher's website. 00aBible.pOld TestamentlHebrew. 0aMasorah. 0aHebrew languagexGrammar.1 aCrowther, Daniel J.,eeditor.1 aHornkohl, Aaron D.,eeditor.1 aKhan, Geoffrey,eeditor.2 aUniversity of Cambridge.bFaculty of Asian and Middle Eastern Studies.2 aOpen Book Publishers,epublisher. 0aSemitic languages and cultures ;vv. 15.x2632-691440uhttps://doi.org/10.11647/OBP.0330zConnect to e-book42uhttps://cdn.openbookpublishers.com/covers/10.11647/obp.0330.jpgzConnect to cover image06466nam a2200481 i 99100672512970896620250313114127.0m     o  d        cr  n         221125t20222022enka    s     001 0 eng d  z9781800647091 (Hardback)  z9781800647084 (Paperback)  a9781800647107q(pdf)  a9781800647145q(HTML)  a9781800647138q(XML)  a9781800647114q(epub)  a9781800647121q(azw3)  aStSaULbengerda00aWomen and migration(s) IIh[electronic resource] /cedited by Kalia Brooks, Cheryl Finley, Ellyn Toscano and Deborah Willis.3 aWomen and migrations two 1aCambridge :bOpen Book Publishers,c2022. 4c©2022  a1 online resource (xxiv, 382 pages) :b128 illustrations.  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  aAvailable through Open Book Publishers.  aOpen access resource providing free access.  aMode of access: World Wide Web.  aThis work is licensed under an Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0 International (CC BY-NC 4.0) license. For more detailed information consult the publisher's website.  aLinks to additional resources are available from the publisher's website.  aIncludes index.0 aIntroduction / Kalia Brooks, Deborah Willis, Ellyn Toscano, Cheryl Finley -- 1. Carry Over / Sama Alshaibi  2. Marie Louise Christophe --      Firelei Báez -- 3. Astral Sea / Tsedaye Makonnen -- 4. Maid in the USA / Carolina Mayorga -- 5. Rapture / Shirin Neshat -- 6. Ble