 continent's past. Beyond the provision of historical content, this textbook equips students with the intellectual tools to interrogate prevailing accounts of European history, and enables them to seek out additional perspectives in a bid to further enrich the discipline."--Publisher's website. 0aEuropexCivilization. 0aEuropexHistory.1 aHansen, Jan,eeditor.1 aHung, Jochen,eeditor.1 aIra, Jaroslav,eeditor.1 aKlement, Judit,eeditor.1 aLesage, Sylvain,eeditor.1 aSimal, Juan Luis,eeditor.1 aTompkins, Andrew,eeditor.2 aOpen Book Publishers,epublisher.40uhttps://doi.org/10.11647/OBP.0323zConnect to e-book42uhttps://cdn.openbookpublishers.com/covers/10.11647/obp.0323.jpgzConnect to cover image05066nam a2200493 i 99100711237970896620250313114125.0m        d        cr  n         230307 20232023enka    sb    001 0 eng d  z9781800647732 (Hardback)  z9781800647725 (Paperback)  a9781800647749q(pdf)  a9781800647787q(HTML)  a9781800647770q(XML)  a9781800647756q(epub)  a9781800647763q(azw3)  a(OCoLC)1372397104  aStSaULbengerda1 aenghnonanon1 aPettit, Edward,d1968-eauthor,etranslator.10aEdda.lEnglish14aThe Poetic Eddah[electronic resource] :ba dual-language edition /cEdward Pettit. 1aCambridge :bOpen Book Publishers,c2023. 4c©2023  a1 online resource (xvi, 878 pages) :b2 illustrations.  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  aAvailable through Open Book Publishers.  aOpen access resource providing free access.  aMode of access: World Wide Web.  aThis work is licensed under an Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0 International (CC BY-NC 4.0) license. For more detailed information consult the publisher's website.  aIncludes bibliographical references and index.  aTexts in Old Norse with English translations ; introduction and supplementary material in English.0 aIntroduction / Edward Pettit -- Vǫluspá (Codex Regius) / Edward Pettit -- 