d the valkyrie Brynhildr. Each poem is provided with an introduction, synopsis and suggestions for further reading. The Old Norse texts are furnished with a textual apparatus recording the manuscript readings behind this edition's emendations, as well as select variant readings. The accompanying translations, informed by the latest scholarship, are concisely annotated to make them as accessible as possible. As the first open-access, single-volume parallel Old Norse edition and English translation of the Poetic Edda, this book will prove a valuable resource for students and scholars of Old Norse literature. It will also interest those researching other fields of medieval literature (especially Old English and Middle High German), and appeal to a wider general audience drawn to the myths and legends of the Viking Age and subsequent centuries."--Publisher's website. 0aEddasxHistory and criticism. 0aEddasvTranslations into English. 0aOld Norse poetryvTranslations into English. 0aMythology, NorsexPoetryvTranslations into English.2 aOpen Book Publishers,epublisher.40uhttps://doi.org/10.11647/OBP.0308zConnect to e-book42uhttps://cdn.openbookpublishers.com/covers/10.11647/obp.0308.jpgzConnect to cover image03298nam a2200457 i 99100711245970896620250313114125.0m        d        cr  n         230224 20232023enk     sb    001 0beng d  z9781800647169 (Hardback)  z9781800647152 (Paperback)  a9781800647176q(pdf)  a9781800647213q(HTML)  a9781800647206q(XML)  a9781800647183q(epub)  a9781800647190q(azw3)  a(OCoLC)741968808  aStSaULbengerda1 aGraham, P. J.q(Philip Jeremy),eauthor.10aSusan Isaacsh[electronic resource] :ba life freeing the minds of children /cPhilip Graham.  aSecond edition. 1aCambridge :bOpen Book Publishers,c2023. 4c©2023  a1 online resource (xxviii, 354 pages)   atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  aAvailable through Open Book Publishers.  