dimension to the Medieval book. She gives the reader the opportunity to reflect on the social, anthropological and historical value of the use of the book by sharpening our senses to the way users handled books in different situations. Rudy has amassed an incredible amount of material for this research and the way in which she presents each manuscript conveys an approach that scholars on Medieval history and book materiality should keep in mind when carrying out their own research. What perhaps is most striking in her articulate text, is how she expresses that the touching of books was not without emotion, and the accumulated effects of these emotions are worthy of preservation, study and further reflection."--Publisher's website.  0aBooksxHistoryy400-1450. 0aManuscripts, MedievalxHistory and criticism. 0aCodicology. 0aBooksxHistoryy1450-1600. 0aMaterial culturexResearch.2 aOpen Book Publishers,epublisher.0 aSocial encounters with the book.40uhttps://doi.org/10.11647/OBP.0337zConnect to e-book42uhttps://cdn.openbookpublishers.com/covers/10.11647/obp.0337.jpgzConnect to cover image04645nam a2200589 i 99100747695970896620250313114125.0m        d        cr  n         230509t20232023enka    sb    001 0beng d  z9781805110194 (hardback)  z9781805110187 (paperback)  a9781805110200q(pdf)  a9781805110248q(HTML)  a9781805110217q(epub)  a9781805110224q(AZW3)  a9781805110231q(XML)  a(OCoLC)1389612807  aStSaULbengerda  ae-uk---1 aRobinson, Andrew,d1957-eauthor.14aThe last man who knew everythingh[electronic resource] :bThomas Young, the anonymous polymath who proved Newton wrong, explained how we see, cured the sick, and deciphered the Rosetta stone, among other feats of genius /cAndrew Robinson ; [with a foreword by Martin Rees].  aRevised edition. 1aCambridge :bOpen Book Publishers,c[2023] 4c©2023  a1 online resource (xxx, 266 pages) :b17 colour illustrations.   atextbtxt2rdacontent  astill 