 violent behaviour and its causes, without prejudging what these might be."--Publisher's website.20aCommonwealth Commission on Respect and Understanding. 0aPeacexInternational cooperationy21st century. 0aConflict managementxInternational cooperationy21st century. 0aDemocratizationy21st century. 0aNation-buildingxInternational cooperationy21st century. 0aSecurity, InternationalxInternational cooperationy21st century.1 aSen, Amartya,d1933-eeditor.2 aCommonwealth Secretariat,epublisher.2 aCommonwealth Commission on Respect and Understanding.tCivil paths to peace.2 aOpen Book Publishers,epublisher. 0aOpen reports series ;vv. 1.x2399-667640uhttps://doi.org/10.11647/OBP.0014zConnect to e-book42uhttps://cdn.openbookpublishers.com/covers/10.11647/obp.0014.jpgzConnect to cover image04904nam a2200433 i 99100947415970896620250313114125.0m        d        cr cnu---unuuu121120t20112011enka    sb    001 0 eng d  z9781906924379 (Hardback)  z9781906924362 (Paperback)  a9781906924386q(pdf)  a1906924384q(pdf)  a(OCoLC)794698071   aStSaULbengerda00aHenry James's Europeh[electronic resource] :bheritage and transfer /cedited by Dennis Tredy, Annick Duperray and Adrian Harding. 1aCambridge :bOpen Book Publishers,c[2011] 4c©2011  a1 online resource (xxiv, 292 pages) :billustrations.  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  aAvailable through Open Book Publishers.  aOpen access resource providing free access.  aMode of access: World Wide Web.  aHenry James's Europe: Heritage and Transfer is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution-Noncommercial-No Derivative Works 2.0 UK: England & Wales License. For more detailed information consult the publisher's website.  aDescription based on print version record.  aIncludes bibliographical references (pages 273-286) and index.0 aPreface / Dennis Tredy -- On 'The European Society of Jamesian Studies' / Adr