ble from the publisher's website.   aIncludes bibliographical references (pages 431-434) and index.0 a1. Introducción a la filosofía del limitarismo / Ingrid Robeyns -- 2. Tener demasiado / Ingrid Robeyns -- 3. Los límites a la riqueza en la historia de la filosofía occidental / Matthias KrammIngrid Robeyns -- 4. Razones basadas en la autonomía a favor del limitarismo / Danielle Zwarthoed -- 5. Limitarismo: ¿Patrón, principio o presunción? / Dick Timmer -- 6. Los límites del limitarismo / Robert Huseby -- 7. ¿Por qué el limitarismo? / Ingrid Robeyns -- 8. Limitarismo presuntivo: Una respuesta a Robert Huseby / Dick Timmer -- 9. Suficiencia, límites y perspectivas de umbrales múltiples / Colin Hickey -- 10. Un argumento neorrepublicano a favor del limitarismo / Elena Icardi -- 11. El argumento del autorrespeto a favor del limitarismo / Christian Neuhäuser -- 12. Cambio climático, justicia distributiva y límites "preinstitucionales" a la apropiación de recursos / Colin Hickey -- 13. Límites ecológicos: Ciencia, justicia, políticas y la vida buena /      Fergus Green -- 14. Limitarismo y generaciones futuras / Tim Meijers.  a"'Tener demasiado' es el primer volumen académico dedicado al limitarismo: la idea de que el uso de los recursos económicos o de los ecosistemas no sobrepasen ciertos límites. Se trata de un concepto profundamente arraigado en el pensamiento económico y político, por lo que es posible encontrar premisas similares en pensadores como Platón, Aquino o Spinoza. No obstante, 'Tener demasiado' es el primer ejemplar en el campo de la filosofía política contemporánea en el que el limitarismo se explora en profundidad y con detalle. Asimismo, este estudio reúne por primera vez los mejores escritos de los principales teóricos del limitarismo, lo que le convierte en una contribución esencial al campo de la filosofía política, en general, y de las teorías sobre la justicia distributiva, en particular. Incluye tanto artículos seminales ya publicados como nuevos capítulos y se presenta como lectura indispensable para académicos y estudiantes de teoría política y filosofía, así como para todos aquellos interesados en cuestiones relacionadas con la justicia distributiva."--Publisher's website. 0aLimitarianism (Philosophy) 0aWealth.1 aRobeyns, Ingrid,eeditor. 1 aIñaki, Héctor,etranslator.1 aMárquez, Larrínaga,etranslator.2 aOpen Book Publishers,epublisher.0 aHaving too much : philosophical essays on limitarianism.40uhttps://doi.org/10.11647/OBP.0354zConnect to e-book42uhttps://cdn.openbookpublishers.com/covers/10.11647/obp.0354.jpgzConnect to cover image04036nam a2200397 i 99101497219970896620250313114123.0m     o  d        cr  n         240227t20242024enkad   sb    001 0 eng d  z9781800648852 (hbk.)  z9781800648845 (pbk.)  a9781800648869q(pdf)  a9781800648906q(HTML)  a9781800648876q(EPUB)  a(OCoLC)1423523858  aStSaULbengerda1 aGabler, Hans Walter,d1938-eauthor.10aGenetic inroads into the art of James Joyceh[electronic resource] /cHans Walter Gabler. 1aCambridge :bOpen Book Publishers,c[2024] 4c©2024  a1 online resource (vi, 452 pages) :b9 illustrations, 2 tables.  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  aAvailable through Open Book Publishers.  aOpen access resource providing free access.  aMode of access: World Wide Web.  aThis work is licensed under an Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0 International (CC BY-NC 4.0) license. For more detailed information consult the publisher's website.  aIncludes bibliography (pages 437-444) and index.0 aIntroduction / Hans Walter Gabler -- Towards a Critical Text of James Joyce's A Portrait of the Artist as a Young Man / Hans Walter Gabler -- The Genesis of A Portrait of the Artist as a Young Man / Hans Walter Gabler -- James Joyce's Dubliners Critical Edition 1993 / Hans Walter Gabler -- James Joyce's A Portrait of the Artist as a Young Man Critical Edition 1993 / Hans Walter Gabler -- Seeing James Joyce's Ulysses into the Digital Age: Forty Years of Steering an Edition Through Turbulences of Scholarship and Reception / Hans Walter Gabler -- James Joyce's Text in Progress / Hans Walter Gabler -- The Rocky Road to Ulysses / Hans Walter Gabler -- James Joyce's Hamlet Chapter / Hans Walter Gabler -- From Hamlet to Scylla & Charybdis: Experience into Art / Hans Walter Gabler -- Emergence of James Joyce's Dialogue Poetics / Hans Walter Gabler -- Structures of Memory and Orientation: Steering a Course Through Wandering Rocks / Hans Walter Gabler --  Composing Penelope Towards the Condition of Music / Hans Walter Gabler -- Ulysses 1922 and the Golden Mean: Shaping His Text Into Book / Hans Walter Gabler -- 'Love, yes. Word known to all men.' / Hans Walter Gabler -- Ulysses 1984: To Edit and Read in Flow of Composition / Hans Walter Gabler.  a"This book is a treasure trove comprising core writings from Hans Walter Gabler's seminal work on James Joyce, spanning fifty years from the analysis of composition he undertook towards a critical text of A Portrait of the Artist as a Young Man, through the Critical and Synoptic Edition of Ulysses, to Gabler's latest essays on (appropriately enough) Joyce's sustained artistic innovation. Not only does this span of essays trace the evolution of Gabler's thinking about Joyce's originality and creative energy. It also reflects the development and maturation of Gabler's own genetic criticism and his methodology of genetic editing, which grows in depth and complexity across the collection. The reader will explore Joyce's life and works through Gabler's incisive eye, while also examining a progress of his reflections on his edition of Ulysses and the past controversy that beset it. This classic compendium combining well-seasoned scholarship and fresh criticism is an essential read for critics of Modernism, digital humanists, scholars and students of Jam