m fellows of Trinity College, it explores various aspects of Byron's life and writing. The collection draws out the relationships between 'memorials, marbles and ruins', themes always prominent in his thinking and feeling. The earliest essay reprinted here dates from the bicentenary of Byron's birth in 1788. Thirty-six years and two centuries later, this collection honours a figure of enduring, complex significance, with whom Trinity College is proud to be associated. It will be of value to scholars and students of Byron, as well as those interested in his life, in the bi-centenary year of his death."--Publisher's website.10aByron, George Gordon Byron,cBaron,d1788-1824.1 aPoole, Adrian,eeditor.2 aOpen Book Publishers,epublisher.40uhttps://doi.org/10.11647/OBP.0399zConnect to e-book42uhttps://cdn.openbookpublishers.com/covers/10.11647/obp.0399.jpgzConnect to cover image05776nam a2200529 i 99101517894970896620250313114120.0m     o  d        cr  n         240402t20242024enka    sb    001 0beng d  z9781800649460 (hbk.)  z9781800649453 (pbk.)  a9781800649477q(pdf)  a9781800649514q(HTML)  a9781800649484q(EPUB)  a(OCoLC)1428180616  aStSaULbengerda  ae-gw---00aNo life without youh[electronic resource] :brefugee love letters from the 1930s : based on the correspondence of Ernst Moritz ("Mope") Felsenstein and Vera Hirsch Felsenstein, 1936-1939 /ccompiled and edited by Franklin Felsenstein ; with an introduction by Rachel Pistol. 1aCambridge :bOpen Book Publishers,c[2024] 4c©2024  a1 online resource (xxii, 622 pages) :b88 colour illustrations.  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  aAvailable through Open Book Publishers.  aOpen access resource providing free access.  aMode of access: World Wide Web.  aThis work is licensed under an Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0 International (CC BY-NC 4.0). license. For more detailed information consult the publisher's website.