scientific disputation of these ideas in the 1930s as they came to be associated with the 'genetic cleansing' of Nazi Germany. This is the first comprehensive study on Norwegian physical anthropology, and its findings shed new light on current political and scientific debates about race across the globe."--Publisher's website. 0aPhysical anthropologyzNorwayxHistory. 0aAnthropometryzNorwayxHistory. 0aCraniometryzNorwayxHistory.12aKyllingstad, Jon Røyne.tKortskaller og langskaller.lEnglish.2 aOpen Book Publishers,epublisher.40uhttps://doi.org/10.11647/OBP.0051zConnect to e-book42uhttps://cdn.openbookpublishers.com/covers/10.11647/obp.0051.jpgzConnect to cover image05797nam a2200433 i 99101545517970896620250313114122.0m        d        cr  n         150217t20152015enka    sb    001 0 eng d  z9781783740635 (Hardback)  z9781783740628 (Paperback)  a9781783740642q(pdf)  a9781783740659q(epub)  a9781783740666q(mobi)  a(OCoLC)904562444   aStSaULbengerda00aFrom dust to digitalh[electronic resource] :bten years of the Endangered Archives Programme /cedited by Maja Kominko. 1aCambridge :bOpen Book Publishers,c[2015] 4c©2015  a1 online resource (lxviii, 654 pages) :bcolour illustrations, colour facsimiles, colour maps.  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  aAvailable through Open Book Publishers.  aOpen access resource providing free access.  aMode of access: World Wide Web.  aThis work as a whole is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution Non-commercial Non-derivative 4.0 International license (CC BY-NC-ND 4.0). For more detailed information consult the publisher's website.  aIncludes bibliography (pages 632-634) and index.0 aAcknowledgements -- List of illustrations -- List of recordings -- Notes on contributors -- Introduction / Lisbet Rousing and Peter Baldwin -- Preserving the past: creating the Endangered Archives Programme / Barry Supple -- 