entified echoes, most of them verbatim, of antecedent texts ranging from major and minor works of English, Irish, Italian, French and other literatures to the poems, plays, popular songs, hymns, comic operas, triple-deckers, dime novels, penny dreadfuls, and print advertisements of his own day. By meticulously identifying hundreds of previously unknown instances of such intertextual echoes, such conscious or unconscious literary borrowings, Winnick's study complements prior works on Joyce's allusive practices by, among others, Weldon Thornton, Don Gifford, and, most recently and comprehensively, Sam Slote, Marc A. Mamigonian, and John Turner, shedding important new light on Joyce's reading, thematic intentions, and creative technique."--Publisher's website.10aJoyce, James,d1882-1941xCriticism and interpretation.10aJoyce, James,d1882-1941xSources.10aJoyce, James,d1882-1941.tDubliners.10aJoyce, James,d1882-1941.tPortrait of the artist as a young man.10aJoyce, James,d1882-1941.tUlysses.2 aOpen Book Publishers,epublisher.40uhttps://doi.org/10.11647/OBP.0429zConnect to e-book42uhttps://cdn.openbookpublishers.com/covers/10.11647/obp.0429.jpgzConnect to cover image06438nam a2200397 i 99101749617380896620251218101230.0a    s b   000 0dt|251117t20252025enka    sb    000 0deng d  z9781805117025 (Hardback)  z9781805117018 (Paperback)  a9781805117032q(PDF)  a9781805117056q(HTML)  a9781805117049q(EPUB)  aStSaULbengerda00aEducation 2.0 :bchronicles of technological and cultural change in Egypth[electronic resource] /cedited by Linda Herrera.3 aEducation two point zero 1aCambridge :bOpen Book Publishers,c2025. 4c©2025  a1 online resource (xxx, 532 pages) :b59 illustrations.  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomupterbc2rdamedia  avolumebcr2rdacarrier  aAvailable through Open Book Publishers.  aOpen access resource providing free access.  aMode of access: World Wide Web.  aThis work is licensed under the 